This paper deals with adversarial imitation learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on high-dimensional sensory data and manipulation tasks, which are often studied in robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed solution involves a constrained optimization objective, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on challenging tasks, which is often studied in systems and control (cs.SY). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, and cs.SY, in that order.
